.TH "zap_vma_ptes" 9 "zap_vma_ptes" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
zap_vma_ptes \- remove ptes mapping the vma
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" zap_vma_ptes
.BI "(struct vm_area_struct *vma "  ","
.BI "unsigned long address "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vma" 12
vm_area_struct holding ptes to be zapped
.IP "address" 12
starting address of pages to zap
.IP "size" 12
number of bytes to zap
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function only unmaps ptes assigned to VM_PFNMAP vmas.

The entire address range must be fully contained within the vma.
